com.gemalto.idp.mobile.oob.message

Interface OobAcknowledgeCallback


  • public interface OobAcknowledgeCallback
    OOB message acknowledgment completed (either success or failure) handler.

    Used by the asynchronous variant of the message acknowledgment - see the OobMessageManager.acknowledgeMessage(OobIncomingMessage, OobAcknowledgeCallback) method.

    Since:
    4.0

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void onAcknowledgeResult(OobResponse response)
      Be called as soon as the acknowledgment process completes.

    • Method Detail

      • onAcknowledgeResult

        void onAcknowledgeResult(OobResponse response)
        Be called as soon as the acknowledgment process completes.

        It is guaranteed that:

        • This method is called on the main UI thread, so that the UI code can directly act on it.
        • This method is called always, regardless the result of the operation, so that the UI code does not have to implement any timeout upon it.
        • This method is never called from within the context of the acknowledgment method - i.e. always after the acknowledgment method returns.
        Parameters:
        response - The OOB acknowledgment response object carrying the result of the operation.
